vibe: 2.0

meta:
  name: vibe_v2_format_spec
  description: >
    New v2 format specification plan. Field-by-field definition of the new
    top-level fields, what was removed and why, and import/merge semantics.
  session_id: 2026-03-10-a7f3b2
  created_at: "2026-03-10"
  author: claude
  tags:
    - format
    - specification
    - v2
  status: draft

imports:
  - plans/00_vision.vibe

context:
  problem: |
    The v1 .vibe format has 7 top-level fields plus 5 legacy fields, many of
    which exist to support runtime execution (tools, workflow, validation).
    The v2 format must drop execution semantics and add document-oriented
    fields while keeping what works (vibe, meta, imports, context, artifacts).

  constraints: |
    - Version field must bump to 2.0
    - Must be valid YAML
    - Must be parseable without a custom runtime
    - Field names should be self-documenting
    - Must support the import/merge system (simplified)

  assumptions: |
    - Consumers are AI systems, humans, and execution tools reading the YAML
    - No runtime will "execute" v2 files; they are consumed as data
    - JSON Schema validation is sufficient for structural validation

  scope: |
    Covers the .vibe file format only. Section types, document archetypes,
    and schema JSON are in sibling plan files.

  glossary: |
    - Top-level field: A YAML key at the root of a .vibe document
    - Program IR: v1 concept of merged representation (replaced by simple merge)
    - ADR: Architecture Decision Record, now a first-class field

sections:
  - id: version_bump
    type: specification
    title: Version Declaration
    content: |
      Every v2 .vibe file begins with:

        vibe: 2.0

      Consumers MUST check this field to determine format version.
      v1 files (vibe: 1.0) are not compatible with v2 consumers.
      v2 files are not compatible with v1 runtimes.

  - id: kept_fields
    type: specification
    title: "Fields Kept from v1"
    content: |
      ## vibe (required)
      Version identifier. Changed from 1.0 to 2.0.

      ## meta (recommended)
      Program metadata. Kept but modified:
      - KEPT: name, description
      - REMOVED: repo_root, runtime_min, runtime_max, repo_write_scope
      - ADDED: session_id, created_at, updated_at, author, tags, status

      New meta schema:
        meta:
          name: string                     # Document identifier
          description: string              # Human-readable purpose
          session_id: string               # Links to MCP session (optional)
          created_at: string               # ISO date or datetime
          updated_at: string               # ISO date or datetime (optional)
          author: string                   # "claude", "human", agent id
          tags: [string]                   # Freeform categorization
          status: draft | review | final   # Document lifecycle

      session_id links the document to an MCP session for tracking
      planning work across time. Format: {YYYY-MM-DD}-{6-char-hex}.

      ## imports (optional)
      Array of .vibe file paths. Simplified from v1:
      - No Program IR compilation step
      - Merge is simple field union (last writer wins for scalars, concat for arrays)
      - Circular imports are an error
      - Relative paths resolved from importing file's directory

      ## context (optional)
      Kept and expanded:
      - KEPT: problem, constraints, glossary
      - ADDED: assumptions, scope
      - Freeform additional keys still allowed

      ## artifacts (optional)
      Kept and modified:
        artifacts:
          - path: string                   # File or directory path
            kind: string                   # python, typescript, markdown, yaml, etc.
            description: string            # NEW: what this artifact is for
            depends_on: [string]           # Artifact paths this depends on
            acceptance_criteria: [string]  # NEW: when is this artifact done
            status: planned | in_progress | complete  # NEW: tracking

      REMOVED from artifacts: ownership, write_policy, invariants
      (These were execution concerns. Acceptance criteria replaces invariants
      as a human/AI-reviewable equivalent.)

  - id: removed_fields
    type: specification
    title: "Fields Removed from v1"
    content: |
      ## tools (REMOVED)
      Tool definitions with schemas. These are execution concerns handled
      by whatever tool runs the plan. VIBE documents don't need to know
      what tools exist.

      ## workflow (REMOVED)
      Workflow mode, steps, gates, retry policies. This was the core of
      v1's execution model. Replaced by sections (for document structure)
      and quality (for success criteria).

      ## validation (REMOVED)
      Post-execution validators. Replaced by quality criteria which are
      reviewed by humans/AI rather than executed by a runtime.

      ## Legacy fields (ALL REMOVED)
      sources, scope, constraints, transforms, handoff -- these were
      already deprecated in v1 and are fully removed in v2.

  - id: new_fields
    type: specification
    title: "New Fields in v2"
    content: |
      ## sections (optional)
      Ordered list of document sections. Replaces workflow.steps.

        sections:
          - id: string           # Unique within document
            type: string         # analysis, design, decision, specification, risk, checklist
            title: string        # Human-readable heading
            content: string      # Multiline YAML string (the actual content)
            depends_on: [string] # Section IDs this builds on (optional)

      Sections are the body of a .vibe document. They contain the actual
      planning content, organized by type. See 20_document_types.vibe for
      the type system.

      ## decisions (optional)
      First-class Architecture Decision Records.

        decisions:
          - id: string           # Unique within document
            title: string        # One-line summary
            status: string       # proposed, accepted, deprecated, superseded
            context: string      # Why this decision is needed
            options:             # Alternatives considered
              - name: string
                description: string
            chosen: string       # Name of chosen option
            rationale: string    # Why this option was chosen
            consequences: [string]  # What follows from this choice

      Decisions were implicit in v1 (buried in context or step goals).
      Making them first-class enables tracking, searching, and linking.

      ## quality (optional)
      Quality criteria that define "done". Replaces validation.

        quality:
          - id: string           # Unique within document
            type: string         # review, test, metric, checklist
            description: string  # What is being checked
            criteria: string     # How to determine pass/fail

      Unlike v1 validators which were executed by a runtime, quality
      criteria are evaluated by humans or AI reviewers. They describe
      what good looks like rather than how to check it programmatically.

  - id: import_merge
    type: specification
    title: Import and Merge Semantics
    content: |
      v2 simplifies v1's Program IR compilation into straightforward merge:

      1. Load the root .vibe file
      2. For each path in imports, load that file recursively
      3. Merge fields using these rules:
         - vibe: root file's version wins
         - meta: root file wins (no merge)
         - imports: not merged (already resolved)
         - context: deep merge (root keys override imported keys)
         - artifacts: concatenate arrays, deduplicate by path (root wins)
         - sections: concatenate arrays (root appended after imports)
         - decisions: concatenate arrays, deduplicate by id (root wins)
         - quality: concatenate arrays, deduplicate by id (root wins)

      Circular import detection: maintain a visited set during resolution.
      If a file appears twice in the import chain, raise an error.

      Path resolution: import paths are relative to the importing file's
      directory, not the repository root (unless they start with /).

decisions:
  - id: dec_version_bump
    title: Bump version to 2.0 (not 1.1 or 1.5)
    status: proposed
    context: |
      The format changes are not backward compatible. v1 consumers will
      not understand v2 files and vice versa.
    options:
      - name: minor_bump
        description: Use 1.1 to suggest evolution
      - name: major_bump
        description: Use 2.0 to signal breaking change
    chosen: major_bump
    rationale: |
      Removing three top-level fields (tools, workflow, validation) and
      adding three new ones (sections, decisions, quality) is a breaking
      change. A major version bump communicates this clearly.
    consequences:
      - Consumers must check version field
      - No migration path within the format itself
      - Clean break from v1 semantics

  - id: dec_merge_simplify
    title: Simplify merge semantics (drop Program IR)
    status: proposed
    context: |
      v1 defined a complex Program IR with deterministic merge rules for
      every field including tools and workflow steps. v2 has fewer fields
      and no execution semantics to merge.
    options:
      - name: keep_ir
        description: Keep Program IR concept with updated field list
      - name: simple_merge
        description: Drop IR, use straightforward field-level merge rules
    chosen: simple_merge
    rationale: |
      Program IR existed to support deterministic execution. Without
      execution, simple merge rules (union for arrays, root wins for
      scalars) are sufficient and much easier to implement.
    consequences:
      - Drop PROGRAM_IR.md spec document
      - Create MERGE_SEMANTICS.md with simplified rules
      - Import resolution is a simple recursive load

quality:
  - id: q_format_complete
    type: review
    description: All v2 fields are fully specified
    criteria: |
      - Every field has a type, description, and example
      - Required vs optional is clear for each field
      - Removed fields are listed with rationale
      - New fields have enough detail to implement a schema

  - id: q_backward_compat
    type: review
    description: Breaking changes are clearly documented
    criteria: |
      - Version bump rationale is explicit
      - No ambiguity about v1 vs v2 compatibility
      - Migration guidance references 60_migration.vibe
